    "Apply per-peer and per-kind rate and size budgets"
    "Keep INAC from becoming a parallel authority system"]
   :status :partial
   :implemented ["Receiver-side remote WSS INAC allowlist for Artifact Delivery offer frames"
                 "Receiver-side remote WSS push gate for inline `inac.invitation` capability passports"
                 "Receiver-side invitation authorization uses the shared `capability-binding::authorize` path with `OperationRequest::InacPush`"
                 "Receiver-side general push authorization uses the shared `capability-binding::authorize` path with the built-in `inac-push@v1` evaluator"
                 "Receiver-side Memarium custody authorization uses the shared `capability-binding::authorize` path with the built-in `memarium-custody@v1` evaluator"
                 "Custody transport limits enforce `max_bytes` before AD admission and durable `max_records` consumption in `<data-dir>/storage/inac.sqlite`"
                 "`inac-invitation@v1` scope evaluator with `inac/push`, peer, schema, artifact id, content type, and single-use semantics"
                 "Single-use invitation consumption and transfer decisions are persisted in `<data-dir>/storage/inac.sqlite`"
