 :notes
 ["INAC has a schema-gated local MVP scaffold and WSS peer-message transport, but is not yet a complete peer protocol."
  "The runtime fails closed without an explicit authoritative handler for an artifact kind."
  "Remote WSS INAC receiver policy now fails closed: `offer` remains behind explicit peer allowlists, while `push` requires either an explicit allowlist or an inline capability passport authorized as invitation, generic INAC push, or Memarium custody."
  "Direct `inac.offer`, `inac.request`, and `inac.push` host capabilities are governed by INAC outbound allowlists; Artifact Delivery routes that resolve to `inac-direct` are governed by Artifact Delivery outbound allowlists."
  "Referenced payload slots are schema-valid; Artifact Delivery can resolve `artifact-store:`, Memarium, and explicitly allowed `agora-record:` references before admission. `inac-peer-artifact:` peer object-store lookup remains future work."
  "The local host/operator surface now includes `/v1/inac/status` and `/admin/inac`; this is observability, not peer transport completion."
  "Invitation notification delivery uses the local notification queue: Accept issues a narrow invitation passport and Reject records a local denial; this is a local UX flow, not a second authority system."
  "Matrix mailbox transport remains required before asynchronous store-and-forward peer exchange. Raw binary-frame streaming is an optimization over the current peer-message stream carrier, not a prerequisite for byte-identical large payload transfer."]}
